    assistant_response: "Incidents classified as a major incident include:\n\n1. **Customer Impact**: Significant numbers of customers affected or displaced, sustained disruption across customer types and brands, or high-profile/high-value single customers impacted [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=5].\n\n2. **Network & Systems Impact**: Severe network or property impact, systems unavailable for a long period with material impact, or catastrophic dual cable failure [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=5].\n\n3. **Natural Disasters**: Catastrophic events such as cyclones, storms, bushfires, floods, or extreme temperatures (declared heatwave) [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=6].\n\n4. **Security Breaches**: Company-wide security or data breaches [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=6].\n\n5. **National or Environmental Significance**: Issues of national significance, acts of sabotage/terrorism, or major safety/environmental incidents [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=6].\n\n6. **Media Awareness**: High media awareness and interest across multiple platforms [incident_management_framework.pdf#page=7]."
